comment: LlamaStash README/site demo — the init wizard driven interactively,
comment: then a TUI tour, with the Lemonade (NPU) backend enabled so the dashboard
comment: shows both engines.
comment: Flow: `llamastash init` answered by hand (existing llama-server, a small
comment: model pasted by HF id), then "Launch the TUI now?" hands straight into the
comment: TUI: launch gemma-4-E2B on llama.cpp, start qwen3.5-4b-FLM on the Lemonade
comment: NPU (running 3, dual backend), HuggingFace pull, theme cycle, chat gemma.
comment:
comment: Prereq: a daemon started with the Lemonade backend, e.g.
comment:   target/release/llamastash daemon start --lemonade   # spawns lemond on :13305
comment:
comment: Capture (release binary symlinked as `llamastash` on PATH, 131x34 to match
comment: assets/tui.gif, against the real daemon for a rich dashboard):
comment:   ln -sf "$PWD/target/release/llamastash" /tmp/ls-demo-bin/llamastash
comment:   PATH=/tmp/ls-demo-bin:$PATH /tmp/ls-tui-venv/bin/python \
comment:     scripts/tui/harness.py scripts/tui/demo.prog /tmp/ls-demo-out \
comment:     /usr/bin/zsh -i --cast /tmp/ls-demo-out/demo.raw.cast --cols 131 --rows 34
comment: Then trim idle gaps and render:
comment:   scripts/tui/trim_cast.py demo.raw.cast assets/demo.cast --end <T>
comment:   agg --font-size 16 assets/demo.cast assets/tui.gif
comment: Stills + init.gif come from the same cast (see cast_frames.py):
comment:   cast_frames.py frame assets/demo.cast 15.6 assets/tui_2.png
comment:   cast_frames.py clip assets/demo.cast /tmp/init.cast --end 7.8
comment:   agg --font-size 16 /tmp/init.cast assets/init.gif

# ── let the shell paint its prompt, then start the wizard ──
wait:2.5
type:llamastash init
key:enter
wait:3

# ── Install method: pick "Use existing binary" (3rd option) ──
key:down
wait:0.5
key:down
wait:0.7
key:enter
wait:2.5

# ── Pick a model: walk down to "Paste an HF repo id…" (below the 10 picks) ──
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.25
key:down
wait:0.6
key:enter
wait:1.5

# ── paste a small model's HF id (single file via :filename, so it's quick) ──
type:lmstudio-community/gemma-4-E2B-it-GGUF:gemma-4-E2B-it-Q4_K_M.gguf
wait:0.8
key:enter
wait:4

# ── Write config? → Yes ──
key:enter
wait:1.5

# ── Patch AI tool configs? → leave all unchecked, just confirm ──
key:enter
wait:7

# ── Launch the TUI now? → Yes (hands straight into the TUI) ──
key:enter
wait:5

# ── launch gemma-4-E2B on llama.cpp (Home→lemond, ↓↓→gemma in Favorites; no filter) ──
key:home
wait:0.4
key:down
wait:0.4
key:down
wait:0.7
key:enter
wait:1.5
key:enter
wait:11

# ── chat gemma right after launching it (it is auto-selected; r collapses reasoning) ──
type:C
wait:1.5
type:r
wait:0.5
type:e
type:Hello
wait:1.2
key:enter
wait:14

# ── leave the chat, pull from HuggingFace: search by name, show results ──
key:esc
wait:0.5
key:esc
wait:0.5
key:esc
wait:1
type:P
wait:2
type:Qwen3
wait:3.5
key:esc
wait:0.5
key:esc
wait:0.5
key:esc
wait:1.2

# ── cycle through all five themes, landing back on Macchiato ──
type:t
wait:1.2
type:t
wait:1.2
type:t
wait:1.2
type:t
wait:1.2
type:t
wait:1.5

# ── finally, jump to the bottom and start the Lemonade NPU model (dual backend) ──
key:end
wait:1
key:enter
wait:1.5
key:enter
wait:9
# end on the Lemonade model coming up (cast trimmed here; harness tears the TUI down)
wait:2
